wikipedia_page.main: Helen Joy Stother (21 June 1955 – 8 October 2019) was an English cricketer and former member of the England women's cricket team who played as a right-arm medium bowler. She appeared in 7 Test matches and 12 One Day Internationals between 1982 and 1986. She played domestic cricket for Sussex and Middlesex.
